{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GaGW4CJdsfPR8fJDFvdp3R","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Line 417: `if (isSectionLabel(text)) return false;` — so `passesHardFilters` DOES call `isSectionLabel`. And `SECTION_LABELS` includes `\"vegetables\"`, `\"fish & seafood\"`, etc.\n\nSo why do `VEGETABLES` and `FISH & SEAFOOD` pass hard filters?\n\nLet me think... `isSectionLabel` normalizes the text: `stripDiacritics(text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase())`.\n\n- `\"VEGETABLES\"` → normalized → `\"vegetables\"` → which IS in SECTION_LABELS. So it should be filtered!\n\n\n- `\"FISH & SEAFOOD\"` → normalized → `\"fish & seafood\"` → which IS in SECTION_LABELS. So it should be filtered!\n\nBut the feedback shows these are being extracted as candidates, which means the plan's root cause analysis might be off. Let me look at the actual feedback again — it mentions these are ALL-CAPS category headers and mid-document instruction lines, so maybe the issue isn't with the hard filters themselves but with how the text is being processed before it reaches them.\n\nLooking at the specific examples, the feedback is pointing out that after the section headers like `VEGETABLES` and `FISH & SEAFOOD`, the extractor is picking wrong lines as titles instead. So the headers ARE being filtered correctly, but the extractor fails to identify the actual title that comes after them. The plan's analysis about Polish food categories and their English equivalents seems to be missing the real problem — it's not about which labels pass the filters, it's about what happens when the extractor tries to find the title after a filtered header. So `VEGETABLES` actually does get filtered out by `passesHardFilters`, which means Fix 2 is based on a misdiagnosis. If those section labels are already being excluded, then the real problem for the Pattern 2 failures must lie elsewhere—maybe the direct-successor bonus logic or something in how candidates are being ranked. Let me trace through what should actually happen with the real titles like \"Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\" and \"Roasted Asparagus with Parmesan\" if they're passing the hard filters.\n\nLooking back at the iteration history, the direct-successor bonus was added in iteration 28, but it doesn't account for blank lines when checking the previous line. That's likely the actual culprit for why wrong lines are winning—Fix 3 is what really needs to happen here.\n\nActually, let me reconsider whether the section header filtering is even working correctly. If the direct-successor bonus checks whether the previous line is a section label using `isSectionLabel`, it should already trigger for `VEGETABLES` since that function would identify it as a header. Let me trace through the iteration 28 implementation to see how it's actually checking the previous line...\n\nChecking the bonus logic...\n\nFor Halibut, the previous line is blank, so none of the header checks match and the bonus doesn't fire. For Roasted Asparagus, the same issue occurs—there's a blank line between the section header and the item, so the direct-successor bonus never activates. Fix 3, which skips over blank lines when looking for the previous header, would resolve both cases.\n\nLooking at Fix 3 more carefully, it adds `isCategorySectionLabel` to the predecessor check, but that's actually redundant since `isSectionLabel` already handles `VEGETABLES` and `FISH & SEAFOOD`. The real fix is just the backward scan past blank lines—the additional category label check isn't necessary for these cases. I need to verify that `\"fish & seafood\"` is actually in `SECTION_LABELS` and trace through the normalization logic to confirm `isSectionLabel` would catch it. Since it does, the entire premise of Fix 2 is flawed — the real issue is the blank-line problem that Fix 3 identifies, so I should revise the plan to remove the unnecessary `isCategorySectionLabel` checks and rely on the existing `isSectionLabel` validation instead. the third case. For Ogórkowa Zupa, the plan says the title is `OGÓRKOWA ZUPA` at line 3, preceded by pipe-separated metadata at line 1 and a blank line. The direct-successor bonus should fire if the blank-line skip is implemented (Fix 3). The metadata line `Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | ...` is already filtered by `text.includes(\" | \")` in `passesHardFilters`.\n\nSo for all 3 Pattern 2 failures, the fix is just Fix 3 (blank-line skip in direct-successor bonus). Fix 2 is unnecessary.\n\nNow I'm realizing that if Fix 2 doesn't actually solve anything, I need to reconsider what it was supposed to address. Looking back, `VEGETABLES` and `FISH & SEAFOOD` are already in `SECTION_LABELS` and already caught by the hard filters, so removing Fix 2 entirely makes sense. For Fix 3, I can simplify it to just scan backward past blank lines without the extra category checks—`isSectionLabel` already handles those cases. I should also add some cross-iteration context to Fix 5 about the underlying tension.\n\nAnd I still need to resolve the open question about how `isTitleAbsentPage` interacts with `findBurstEnd`. Let me finalize the plan now.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":428,"cache_read_input_tokens":67632,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":428},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7a8a1052-f060-407b-8164-bf7c5f97f8a0","uuid":"28656e7a-bd9e-45ff-90f8-6f43fb6a2369"}
